# GRC Compliance Webapp — SumiRiko Italy S.p.A.
# Aggiornato: marzo 2026

## Stack
Backend : Python 3.11 · Django 5.1 · DRF · Celery 5 · Redis 7 · PostgreSQL 15
Frontend: React 18 · TypeScript · Vite 5 · Tailwind · Recharts · i18next · Zustand · TanStack Query

## Moduli implementati (M00–M20 + estensioni)
M00 Governance       — RoleAssignment, SecurityCommittee, NormativeRole
M01 Plants           — Plant, BusinessUnit, PlantFramework (max 1 livello nesting)
M02 RBAC             — GrcRole (7 ruoli), UserPlantAccess, ExternalAuditorToken
M03 Controls         — Framework, Control, ControlInstance, ControlMapping
                       export_engine.py → SOA ISO27001 / VDA ISA TISAX / NIS2 Matrix
M04 Assets           — Asset, AssetIT, AssetOT, NetworkZone, change_ref fields
M05 BIA              — CriticalProcess (MTPD/MBCO/RTO/RPO), TreatmentOption, RiskDecision
M06 Risk             — RiskAssessment (inerente+residuo), RiskDimension, RiskMitigationPlan
                       RiskAppetitePolicy — soglie configurabili
M07 Documents        — Document (document_type), DocumentVersion, Evidence (evidence_type)
M08 Tasks            — Task (source_id+source_module), TaskComment, escalation chain
M09 Incidents        — Incident, RCA, IncidentNotification, close→PDCA+LessonLearned auto
M10 Audit Trail      — AuditLog (hash chain SHA-256, trigger append-only PostgreSQL)
M11 PDCA             — PdcaCycle, PdcaPhase, close_cycle→aggiorna sorgente+LessonLearned
M12 Lessons          — LessonLearned (propagazione cross-plant)
M13 Management Review— ManagementReview (snapshot dettagliato), report HTML scaricabile
M14 Suppliers        — Supplier, SupplierAssessment
M15 Training         — TrainingCourse, TrainingEnrollment, PhishingSimulation (KnowBe4)
M16 BCP              — BcpPlan (RTO/RPO vs MTPD BIA), BcpTest (test_type+objectives)
M17 Audit Prep       — AuditPrep (soft delete+annulla), EvidenceItem, AuditFinding
                       AuditProgram — calendario annuale audit
M18 Reporting        — ComplianceSummary, RiskSummary, OwnerReport (BarChart)
M19 Notifications    — NotificationSubscription (3 non disattivabili), WebhookEndpoint
M20 AI Engine        — AiInteractionLog, Sanitizer (PII), AiRouter (local/cloud)

## Moduli aggiuntivi (oltre M00–M20)
compliance_schedule  — ComplianceSchedulePolicy, ScheduleRule (23 tipi),
                       RequiredDocument, get_activity_schedule(), get_due_date()
                       Frontend: ActivitySchedulePage, RequiredDocumentsPage, SchedulePolicyPage

## Regole architetturali ASSOLUTE — non derogare mai
1.  Tutti i model ereditano da core.models.BaseModel (UUID pk, soft_delete, timestamps, created_by)
2.  Business logic SOLO in services.py — mai nelle views o nei serializer
3.  Ogni azione rilevante chiama core.audit.log_action(action_code, level, entity, payload)
4.  AuditLog append-only — trigger PostgreSQL + select_for_update() in _get_prev_hash()
5.  Soft delete sempre (soft_delete()) — mai queryset.delete() diretto
6.  Nessuna query N+1 — select_related/prefetch_related obbligatori
7.  Task assegnati a ruolo (risoluzione dinamica via UserPlantAccess), mai a utente diretto
8.  Framework normativi = JSON in backend/frameworks/ — non hardcodare controlli nel codice
9.  M20 AI: nessun PII al cloud senza Sanitizer.sanitize(), human-in-the-loop sempre
10. Scadenze calcolate con compliance_schedule.services.get_due_date() — mai hardcodate

## Pattern obbligatori

### Service pattern
def my_service(obj, user, **kwargs):
    # logica business
    obj.field = value
    obj.save(update_fields=["field", "updated_at"])
    log_action(user=user, action_code="module.action",
               level="L2", entity=obj, payload={...})
    return obj

### Destroy pattern (mai hard delete)
def destroy(self, request, *args, **kwargs):
    instance = self.get_object()
    # controlla dipendenze prima
    instance.soft_delete()
    log_action(..., action_code="module.deleted", level="L2", ...)
    return Response(status=204)

### Celery task pattern
@shared_task(bind=True, autoretry_for=(Exception,),
             max_retries=3, default_retry_delay=60)
def my_task(self):
    try:
        # logica
    except Exception as e:
        import logging
        logging.getLogger(__name__).error(f"Task error: {e}")
        raise

## Livelli audit log
L1 — Critico    (conservazione 5 anni): approvazioni formali, chiusura incidenti NIS2,
                 export SOA/VDA/NIS2, accettazione rischi, token auditor
L2 — Operativo  (conservazione 3 anni): valutazioni controlli, assessment, task, evidenze
L3 — Informativo(conservazione 1 anno): accessi lettura, export non formali, operazioni sistema

## Scadenze — usa sempre get_due_date()
from apps.compliance_schedule.services import get_due_date
# Esempi:
evidence.valid_until    = get_due_date("evidence_screenshot", plant=plant)
finding.deadline        = get_due_date("finding_major", plant=plant)
supplier.next_assessment= get_due_date("supplier_assessment", plant=plant)
plan.next_test_date     = get_due_date("bcp_test", plant=plant)

## Sicurezza — impostazioni attive
JWT: ACCESS=30min, REFRESH=7gg, ROTATE=True
Rate limiting: anon=20/h, user=500/h
Security headers: X_FRAME_OPTIONS=DENY, SECURE_CONTENT_TYPE_NOSNIFF=True
DB pooling: CONN_MAX_AGE=60
Produzione: settings/prod.py con SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT, HSTS, cookie secure

## Export documenti compliance
GET /api/v1/controls/export/?framework=ISO27001&format=soa&plant=<uuid>
GET /api/v1/controls/export/?framework=TISAX_L2&format=vda_isa&plant=<uuid>
GET /api/v1/controls/export/?framework=NIS2&format=compliance_matrix&plant=<uuid>
IMPORTANTE: usare fetch() con header Authorization Bearer, NON window.open()

